          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Elizabeth Port. New Jersey</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <date>19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> November 1851</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Reverend Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir!</p>
                              <p>I have the pleasure to<lb/> acknowledge receipt of your valued
                                        favor; and should<lb/> have answered same but had not time
                                        to do so ere<lb/> this. I delivered your letter to
                                                  <persName>Mr. A D. Haar</persName>. I<lb/> truly
                                        thank you for your kind expressions, I also<lb/> note the
                                        prospectus, and have informed those fewâ€”<lb/>who are living
                                        at this port, a Gentleman has requeste=<lb/>=ed me to
                                        inquire the prices of the sett's of books you<lb/> have at
                                        present, say with name &amp;c complete. I<lb/> enclose you
                                        an Obituary which I shall feel <sic>infinate<lb/>,,ly</sic>
                                        obliged if you would give it publication in<lb/> your
                                        valuable periodical. I also enclose you fifty<lb/> cents for
                                        the two <add>?</add> with many thanks.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I am Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Your Obt Sevt &amp; friend</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">
                                        <persName role="author">Benjamin Lindo</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Reverend Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi>
                                        </placeName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p rend="align(center)">
                                        <sic>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">Obitury</hi>
                                        </sic>
                              </p>
                              <p>Died at <placeName>Elizabeth Port. New Jersey</placeName> on
                                                  <date>22d<lb/> Hisvan 5612</date> corresponding
                                        with the <date>17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> November<lb/>
                                                  1851</date>. <persName>David Bair</persName>, Son
                                        of <persName>Mr. Abraham Bair</persName><lb/> and Grand Son
                                        of <persName>Mr David Haar</persName>, aged<lb/> One year
                                        and nine months, his <sic>corpes</sic> was<lb/> taken to
                                                  <placeName>Williams Burg</placeName> and there
                                        entered<lb/> in the <sic>Portagues</sic> new
                                                  <sic>Buriel</sic> ground, he was<lb/> a fine and
                                        sensible child, peace be to his<lb/> departed soul - - -
                                                  <persName role="author"><hi rend="underline"
                                                  >Benjamin Lindo</hi></persName></p>
